➜International Day of Persons with Disabilities: Respect and love go hand in hand
http://www.sohu.com/a/437004795_162758	28448
<p align="center"><img src="http://p3.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201208/b5cd2b6f7ce948dcaf2021274b178ebc.jpeg" width="633" height="420" /></p>
<p>December 3, 2020 is the 29th International Day of the Disabled. Various localities have carried out various activities to help the disabled. Disabled people are a group with special difficulties and require extra care and attention. They are like bitten apples. Although perfection and completeness cannot have both, they are still struggling towards hope and the future. The picture shows a "Bear Claw" coffee shop on Yongkang Road in Xuhui District, Shanghai. The manager is a deaf barista, and the clerk who delivers coffee with bear claws is a person with facial burns. They use this special way to bring heartwarming service to customers. (Photo by Wang Gang/Guangming Picture)</p>
