➜COVID-19 may cause hundreds of thousands of new AIDS cases worldwide
http://www.sohu.com/a/437004850_162758	28453
<p>Countries should adopt ambitious new targets to deal with AIDS in order to avoid hundreds of thousands of new HIV infections and deaths due to the COVID-19, UNAIDS has warned.</p>
<p>The UNAIDS said that the COVID-19 has further deviated the world’s response to AIDS and has not reached the 2020 target. The agency urges countries to learn from the lessons of underinvestment in health care and strengthen global action to end AIDS and other global health emergencies.</p>
