➜WHO: COVID-19 vaccine is coming soon, testing is still important
http://www.sohu.com/a/437005334_162758	28505
<p>The Director-General of the World Health Organization Tan Desai said at a regular briefing on the new crown epidemic that even if the new crown vaccine starts to be vaccinated, testing will still be a key tool to combat the new crown virus.</p>
<p>While emphasizing the important role played by countries where the new crown virus is now under effective control, Tan Desai said that testing will continue to play an important role during the launch of the new crown vaccine.</p>
<p>Tan Desai said: "Initially, health workers, the elderly and other high-risk groups will give priority to vaccinations. This will still give the virus a lot of room to move, and testing will still be an important tool for pandemic control."</p>
