➜A child is infected with HIV every 100 seconds
http://www.sohu.com/a/437006757_162758	28827
<p>Key HIV services have been disrupted in many countries as a result of the new crown pandemic. A report released by the United Nations Children's Fund pointed out that last year, about every 100 seconds, a child or young person under the age of 20 was infected with HIV. The report calls on governments to "protect, sustain and accelerate" efforts to fight HIV infection in children. The report, entitled "Rethinking resilient HIV responses for children, adolescents and pregnant women with HIV", says that prevention and treatment for children are still among the lowest among the major affected groups. In 2019, just under half of the world's children will not have access to life-saving treatment.</p>
<p>[责任编辑: 张舟 ] </p>
